casebody.data:
In re Guardianship of Peck; Peck, f.k.a. Johnson, Appellant; Meraglio, Gdn., Appellee.

[Cite as In re Guardianship of Peck, 109 Ohio St.3d 1203, 2006-Ohio-2182.]

(No. 2005-1061 Submitted March 29, 2006 Decided May 17, 2006.) Joseph R. Ulrich Co., L.P.A., and Kenneth J. Cahill, for appellant. Reminger & Reminger Co., L.P.A., Clifford C. Masch, and Brian D. Sullivan, for appellee.

{¶ 1} The cause is dismissed, sua sponte, as having been improvidently accepted.

{¶ 2} The court orders that the opinion of the court of appeals may not be cited as authority except by the parties inter se.

Moyer, C.J., Resnick, Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Connor, O’Donnell and Lanzinger, JJ., concur.
